Description: A very clean example of a 1999 (first year issue) Fender Classic 60's Stratocaster in Olympic white. Pots date to late 1998 body and neck dates 1999. It's a great guitar and you don't see to many of this model from the late 90s around. Tinted neck, slab rosewood fingerboard, staggered pole pickups, and vintage style tremolo/saddles. Neck is a thin C shape. Guitar recently restrung and it is set up and ready to play. Comes with original tremolo arm. Guitar has minimal signs of use, a solid 9+/10. A hard case is included, please note the case has protected the guitar well, but one latch is broken and there is considerable wear on the case.
